The paper deals with the computational complexity of write-once Turing machines, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves the analysis of storage and coding schemes, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the equivalence of different complexity classes, which could be relevant to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper mentions the restriction of write-once machines to only write at the end of the tape, which could be related to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
